    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The borough began as part of Ocean Township; European settlement began mid‑17th century under the Monmouth Patent of 1665.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        2
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/Sea_Bright,_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "In 1865 the Long Branch and Sea Shore Railroad reached Sea Bright, turning a fishing hamlet into a New York‑city resort.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        12
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/Sea_Bright,_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "A historic seawall built in the 19th century still protects Sea Bright’s shoreline from erosion and storm surges.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        10
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/Sea_Bright,_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "The Peninsula House, moved east in 1884, once hosted celebrity guests and became a symbol of Sea Bright’s “Jewel of the Sea” era.",
